Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.util

Class BaseToObjectValueWriter<E extends Exception>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.util.BaseToObjectValueWriter<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the exception thrown on error.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    AnyValueWriter<E>, ValueWriter<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MessageMetadataParser.TransactionMetadataWriter, PrimitiveOnlyValueWriter, QueryStatusResult.ParameterWriter
    public abstract class BaseToObjectValueWriter<E extends Exception>
extends Object
implements AnyValueWriter<E>
    Base class for converting AnyValue to normal java objects.

    This base class takes care of converting all "normal" java types such as number types, booleans, strings, arrays and lists. It leaves to the extending class to handle neo4j specific types such as nodes, edges and points.

      • entityMode

        public AnyValueWriter.EntityMode entityMode()
        Description copied from interface: AnyValueWriter
        Returns the wanted AnyValueWriter.EntityMode of this AnyValueWriter. A returned AnyValueWriter.EntityMode.REFERENCE signals to all entity-values that they should callback using AnyValueWriter.writeNodeReference(long) or AnyValueWriter.writeRelationshipReference(long) even if the whole entity is available. A returned AnyValueWriter.EntityMode.FULL signals to all entity-values that they can callback using either AnyValueWriter.writeNodeReference(long), AnyValueWriter.writeNode(long, TextArray, MapValue), AnyValueWriter.writeRelationshipReference(long) or AnyValueWriter.writeRelationship(long, long, long, TextValue, MapValue) depending on how much information is available to the value instance.
        Specified by:
        entityMode in interface AnyValueWriter<E extends Exception>
